+## Optional BOSS MCP apply gate
+
+This branch adds a gated BOSS MCP batch-apply orchestrator. It is designed as a controlled execution bridge after JD screening and resume-route selection.
+
+```text
+Original workflow
+JD / link / job table
+        │
+        ▼
+JD parser → route classifier → claim safety gate → resume / message / interview output
+
+New optional extension
+BOSS MCP search/detail or local jobs.json
+        │
+        ▼
+job detail cards printed for review
+        │
+        ▼
+apply gate
+  ├─ dry-run: only render details
+  ├─ manual: ask before each apply
+  └─ auto: explicit opt-in + capped + logged
+        │
+        ▼
+audit log + local dedupe state
+```
+
+Files added:
+
+- `.agents/skills/job-resume-codex/assets/boss_apply_config.example.json`
+- `.agents/skills/job-resume-codex/references/boss_mcp_apply_workflow.md`
+- `.agents/skills/job-resume-codex/scripts/boss_mcp_apply_batch.py`
+
+The default mode is `manual`, and the example config keeps `safety.allow_auto_apply=false`. Auto mode requires a local config change plus the explicit CLI flag `--i-understand-batch-apply`. The script does not include CAPTCHA bypass, login bypass, rate-limit bypass, hidden scraping, or background mass outreach. It only calls the user-configured MCP server and records a local audit log.
